SSyynnooppssiiss
       cc [options] -Kthread file

       #include <synch.h>

       int sema_trywait(sema_t *sema);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       sema_trywait   makes  a  single  attempt  to  acquire  the
       semaphore pointed to by sema.  If the semaphore is  avail-
       able,  sema_trywait  decrements  the  semaphore  value and
       returns to the caller.

       If sema_trywait cannot immediately acquire the  semaphore,
       it  returns  EBUSY  to  the  caller, it does not block the
       caller  to  wait  for  the  semaphore  or  decrement   the
       semaphore value.

   PPaarraammeetteerrss
       pointer to the semaphore to acquire

   sseemmaa ppaarraammeetteerr
       sema  must  have  been  previously  initialized, either by
       sema_init or statically (see sema_init(3synch)).

UUssaaggee
       sema_trywait is used when the  caller  does  not  want  to
       block if the semaphore is unavailable.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       sema_trywait  returns zero for success and an error number
       for failure.

   EErrrroorrss
       If the following condition occurs, sema_trywait fails  and
       returns  the  corresponding value: the semaphore cannot be
       acquired immediately

       If  the  following  condition  is  detected,  sema_trywait
       returns  the  corresponding value: invalid argument speci-
       fied

